Is there a way to reuse attrs?
I have this:
```
&lt;attr name="font" format="enum"&gt;
    &lt;enum name="gotham_book" value="0" /&gt;
    &lt;enum name="gotham_medium" value="1" /&gt;
&lt;/attr&gt;
```

I want to create two other attributes that are the exact same thing as the font attribute, but with different names. Do I have to do it manually?
